tip.text: My fave place ever and am here every weekend. The people are very friendly and the cold brew (white for me) is a must-have. Come earlier, as the place fills up fast on weekends.
Great atmosphere for a weekend brunch. Pity that the aircon broke down while we were there, staff was extremely apologetic and served us iced water immediately. Loved the brunch menu! Will be back!

tip.text: A cozy corner in the neighbourhood, complete with Christmas lights to suit the mood. Buttermilk waffles was fragrant, and mine was tipped with peanut butter crunch ice cream. Love the richness of it.
Amazing waffles in non-conventional flavors. Think red velvet and toffee nut. I love the honey yoghurt gelato with my waffles, drenched in maple syrup and berries compote. A lovely mix!

formattedAddress: Rooftop@#07-00, 171 Syed Alwi Rd (Mustafa Centre (New Extension))

tip.text: Gem of a place in a quiet neighbourhood. Small menu,  didn't get to try the coffee, but their egg mayo crossaint and beef rendang hotdog were good. Will try cakes the next time!
The sister outlet to the Liang Seah St one, this outlet has virtually no crowds and no queue. However, the desserts took quite some time to arrive. Nonetheless, the standard is the same.
